<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Regulation lims:pit-date="2018-07-06" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-07-06" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851808" lims:id="851808" gazette-part="II" regulation-type="SOR" xml:lang="en" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851809" lims:id="851809"><InstrumentNumber>SOR/2018-157</InstrumentNumber><RegistrationDate><Date><YYYY>2018</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>6</DD></Date></RegistrationDate><ConsolidationDate lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></ConsolidationDate><EnablingAuthority lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851811" lims:id="851811"><XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="S-15.3">SPECIES AT RISK ACT</XRefExternal></EnablingAuthority><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851812" lims:id="851812">Critical Habitat of the Northern Bottlenose Whale (Hyperoodon ampullatus) Scotian Shelf Population Order</LongTitle></Identification><Order lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851813" lims:id="851813"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851814" lims:id="851814" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Whereas the Northern Bottlenose Whale (<Language xml:lang="la">Hyperoodon ampullatus</Language>) Scotian Shelf population is a wildlife species that is listed as an endangered species in Part 2 of Schedule 1 to the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="S-15.3">Species at Risk Act</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_a">a</FootnoteRef>;</Text><Footnote id="fn_a" placement="page" status="official"><Label>a</Label><Text>S.C. 2002, c. 29</Text></Footnote></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851815" lims:id="851815" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Whereas the recovery strategy that identified the critical habitat of that species has been included in the Species at Risk Public Registry;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851816" lims:id="851816" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>And whereas a portion of the critical habitat of that species is in a place referred to in subsection 58(2)<FootnoteRef idref="fn_b">b</FootnoteRef> of that Act and, under subsection 58(5) of that Act, that portion must be excluded from the annexed Order;</Text><Footnote id="fn_b" placement="page" status="official"><Label>b</Label><Text>S.C. 2015, c. 10, s. 60</Text></Footnote></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851817" lims:id="851817" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Therefore, the Minister of Fisheries and Oceans, pursuant to subsections 58(4) and (5) of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="S-15.3">Species at Risk Act</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="fn_a">a</FootnoteRef>, makes the annexed <XRefExternal reference-type="regulation" link="SOR-2018-157">Critical Habitat of the Northern Bottlenose Whale (Hyperoodon ampullatus) Scotian Shelf Population Order</XRefExternal>.</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851818" lims:id="851818" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" list-item="no"><Text>Ottawa, July 3, 2018</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851819" lims:id="851819" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="yes" topmarginspacing="12" list-item="no"><TableGroup lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851820" lims:id="851820" bilingual="yes" orientation="portrait" pointsize="11pt" topmarginspacing="50pt" rowbreak="no" spanlanguages="no"><table lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851821" lims:id="851821" frame="none"><tgroup lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851822" lims:id="851822" cols="2"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="100*" /><colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="100.00*" /><tbody lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851823" lims:id="851823"><row rowsep="0"><entry colsep="0" nameend="COLSPEC0" namest="1" rowsep="0" valign="top"><SignatureBlock justification="center" width="20pc"><SignatureTitle justification="center"><Language xml:lang="fr">Le ministre des Pêches et des Océans,</Language></SignatureTitle><SignatureLine justification="center" topmarginspacing="30"><Leader leader="solid" length="20pc" /></SignatureLine><SignatureName justification="center">Dominic LeBlanc</SignatureName><SignatureTitle justification="center"><Language xml:lang="en">Minister of Fisheries and Oceans</Language></SignatureTitle></SignatureBlock></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></TableGroup></Provision></Order><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851824" lims:id="851824"><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851825" lims:id="851825"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851826" lims:id="851826">Application</MarginalNote><Label>1</Label><Text>Subsection 58(1) of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="S-15.3">Species at Risk Act</XRefExternal> applies to the critical habitat of the Northern Bottlenose Whale (<Language xml:lang="la">Hyperoodon ampullatus</Language>) Scotian Shelf population — which is identified in the recovery strategy for that species that is included in the Species at Risk Public Registry — other than the portion of that critical habitat that is in a place referred to in subsection 58(2) of that Act, more specifically, in Zone 1 of the Gully Marine Protected Area as depicted in Schedule 2 to the <XRefExternal reference-type="regulation" link="SOR-2004-112">Gully Marine Protected Area Regulations</XRefExternal>.</Text></Section><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:lastAmendedDate="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851827" lims:id="851827"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2018-07-06" lims:fid="851828" lims:id="851828">Coming into Force</MarginalNote><Label>2</Label><Text>This Order comes into force on the day on which it is registered.</Text></Section></Body></Regulation>